  <h2>Food Pairing Guide</h2>

<p>Kosta Browne Pinot Noir's hallmark elegance and balanced acidity create exceptional versatility at the table. The wine's silky tannins and bright red fruit character, anchored by subtle earth and spice notes, form natural flavor bridges with both rustic and refined cuisine.</p>

<h3>Classic Regional Pairings</h3>
<p>Drawing from Burgundian tradition, <strong>coq au vin</strong> creates a seamless match, where the wine's cherry notes complement the dish while its earthy undertones mirror the mushroom and herb components. Similarly, <strong>duck confit with cherry gastrique</strong> highlights the wine's fruit-forward profile while the rendered fat softens any remaining tannins.</p>

<h3>Flavor Bridge Pairings</h3>
<p><strong>Wild salmon with pinot noir reduction</strong> exemplifies perfect flavor bridging—the wine's natural acidity cuts through the fish's richness while its earthy minerality complements the salmon's clean finish. <strong>Mushroom risotto with truffle oil</strong> creates another harmonious bridge, where the wine's forest floor notes amplify the dish's umami depth.</p>

<p><strong>Herb-crusted rack of lamb</strong> works beautifully as the wine's medium body won't overpower the meat, while its subtle spice notes enhance rosemary and thyme seasonings. The pairing becomes even more refined with a <strong>cherry-port sauce</strong> that directly mirrors the wine's fruit character.</p>

<h3>Versatile Everyday Options</h3>
<p>For casual dining, <strong>grilled portobello burgers</strong> showcase how Kosta Browne's earthy complexity elevates simple ingredients. The wine's acidity cuts through rich toppings like aged gruyère or caramelized onions.</p>

<h3>Special Occasion Selections</h3>
<p><strong>Beef tenderloin with morel mushroom sauce</strong> creates an elegant pairing where the wine's structure supports the meat's richness without competing, while the morels echo the wine's forest floor characteristics. For truly special occasions, <strong>cheese courses featuring aged comté or époisses</strong> allow the wine's complexity to shine, with the cheese's nutty or creamy textures providing textural contrast to the wine's silky mouthfeel.</p>

<p class="bg-wine-50 p-4 text-wine-700">The key to pairing Kosta Browne lies in matching its elegance—avoid overly heavy sauces that mask its nuanced character, instead focusing on ingredients that complement its natural fruit-earth balance.</p>

